CopyQ is clipboard manager with searchable and editable items in history.

For build and install CopyQ see INSTALL file.

To start CopyQ run copyq (creates tray icon). Running this command again will
show CopyQ clipboard history.

To exit application close window or middle-click on tray icon.

Keyboard navigation
===================
PgDown/PgUp,
Home/End,
Up/Down   -- navigation in item list
Ctrl-Up,
Ctrl-Down -- move selected item
Escape    -- hide window
F2        -- edit item
Ctrl-E    -- edit item in external editor
Ctrl-A    -- open action dialog
Delete    -- delete item
Enter     -- put item into clipboard

Type a number to select item with given id.

Type a regular expressions (case-insensitive) to search/filter items.


Configuration
=============
All configuration files are in ~/.config/copyq directory.

copyq.conf:
    editor   -- external editor command
    maxitems -- max items in history

copyq.css:
    Qt stylesheet defining appearance of CopyQ window and item list.

